00:44:13.860 --> 00:44:18.380
But just like the shepherds on the night that we read of in Luke chapter number 2, it was

00:44:18.380 --> 00:44:23.220
given to you, but not to be kept to you.

00:44:23.220 --> 00:44:29.180
It was given to you, and praise God for it, but it was given to you to share with others.

00:44:29.180 --> 00:44:34.660
But maybe this morning there's someone here, maybe there's multiple people here that you've

00:44:34.660 --> 00:44:38.300
never understood who Jesus is.

00:44:38.300 --> 00:44:47.260
You've never understood the consequence of sin, the fact that we do have a holy God that

00:44:47.260 --> 00:44:55.220
does love and is gracious and is merciful and he's holy, but he's just.

00:44:55.220 --> 00:44:58.260
And I'm thankful that he's just.

00:44:58.260 --> 00:45:05.420
And we find this morning that the Bible says that the wages of sin is death, but the gift

00:45:05.420 --> 00:45:11.900
of God is eternal life through Jesus Christ, our Lord.

00:45:11.900 --> 00:45:15.100
We can't get to heaven by our own works.

00:45:15.100 --> 00:45:21.260
Every one of us is going to die one day, as it is appointed unto man once to die.

00:45:21.260 --> 00:45:23.380
After this, the judgment.

00:45:23.420 --> 00:45:30.300
I preached the message last Sunday evening about finishing well, and I said repeatedly,

00:45:30.300 --> 00:45:33.220
we don't know where the finish line is.

00:45:33.220 --> 00:45:36.420
If we were to have a race today, Bart, you and I were going to race.

00:45:36.420 --> 00:45:39.580
I use Zachary as the example on Sunday night.

00:45:39.580 --> 00:45:41.580
We would try to determine where's the finish line.

00:45:41.580 --> 00:45:46.420
I want to know where the finish line is before I start the race, right?

00:45:46.420 --> 00:45:49.420
If we start a race and I say, I won, and he's like, what do you mean?

00:45:49.420 --> 00:45:50.420
I'm like, we got to the finish line.

00:45:50.420 --> 00:45:53.460
I got there before you, but I never told him where it was.

00:45:53.460 --> 00:45:55.700
I went through this Sunday night.

00:45:55.700 --> 00:45:59.180
In the Christian life, we don't know where the finish line is.

00:45:59.180 --> 00:46:04.020
We're all running a race, but we don't know where the finish line is.

00:46:04.020 --> 00:46:06.460
I said this on Sunday night.

00:46:06.460 --> 00:46:14.540
Death can come at any moment, but the rapture can come at any moment.

00:46:14.540 --> 00:46:21.980
Savannah Gardner, I don't think she was 28 years old.

00:46:21.980 --> 00:46:24.620
Her race ended.

00:46:24.620 --> 00:46:30.700
From all I know, she finished well, serving the Lord, faithful.

00:46:30.700 --> 00:46:32.620
You see, it's so young.

00:46:32.620 --> 00:46:34.580
God doeth all things well.

00:46:34.580 --> 00:46:35.580
He knows.

00:46:35.580 --> 00:46:38.100
He has a purpose.

00:46:38.100 --> 00:46:39.100
I don't understand.

00:46:39.100 --> 00:46:40.100
I don't need to understand.

00:46:40.100 --> 00:46:44.700
I just trust God.

00:46:44.700 --> 00:46:46.820
I don't know when your race is going to end.

00:46:46.820 --> 00:46:51.860
If you're saved, live for Jesus, but if you're lost this morning, you've never trusted Christ,

00:46:51.860 --> 00:46:56.300
you've not received that gift, you say, man, I'm looking forward to the gifts I'm going

00:46:56.300 --> 00:46:57.300
to get on Christmas.

00:46:57.300 --> 00:46:58.300
Can I tell you?

00:46:58.300 --> 00:46:59.820
None of that matters.

00:46:59.820 --> 00:47:08.940
The greatest gift is eternal life, and it's been paid for with the blood of Jesus Christ,

00:47:08.940 --> 00:47:17.100
and He offers it to you for whosoever shall call upon the name of the Lord shall be saved.

00:47:17.100 --> 00:47:18.100
Let's pray together.

00:47:18.100 --> 00:47:19.740
Father, we love you.

00:47:19.740 --> 00:47:21.780
We thank you for loving us.

00:47:21.780 --> 00:47:25.900
We thank you so much for the opportunity that you've given us to gather this morning and

00:47:25.900 --> 00:47:36.220
to see once again afresh the greatness of the incarnation, the great promise, the great

00:47:36.220 --> 00:47:42.620
proclamation, and I think about the great purpose.

00:47:42.620 --> 00:47:49.980
God this morning, there may be one or several that are not saved, that have never trusted

00:47:49.980 --> 00:47:53.300
Jesus Christ as their personal Savior.

00:47:53.300 --> 00:47:57.740
I pray that the Holy Spirit of God would convict them of their sin of Christ's righteousness

00:47:57.740 --> 00:47:59.740
and of judgment to come.

00:47:59.740 --> 00:48:03.940
I pray that they would not leave this place without knowing for sure that heaven is their

00:48:03.940 --> 00:48:04.940
home.

00:48:05.540 --> 00:48:09.260
I pray that during this time of invitation for those that are saved, would you help us

00:48:09.260 --> 00:48:13.140
to rejoice in our salvation?

00:48:13.140 --> 00:48:18.780
Would you help us to purpose in sharing the truth of the gospel with others?

00:48:18.780 --> 00:48:23.620
I pray that you would move in these moments as only you can, and we'll thank you for it.

00:48:23.620 --> 00:48:25.380
In Christ's name we pray.

00:48:25.380 --> 00:48:26.380
Would you stand with me?

00:48:26.380 --> 00:48:28.580
Heads are bowed, eyes are closed.

00:48:28.580 --> 00:48:32.380
If you're a man here this morning and you're not sure of heaven, you say, if I were to

00:48:32.380 --> 00:48:34.780
die today, I'm not sure that I'd go to heaven.

00:48:34.780 --> 00:48:39.740
Mark is standing down here with a Bible, and we'd encourage you to come and chat with Brother

00:48:39.740 --> 00:48:43.060
Mark and he'll share some verses with you how you could know for sure that heaven is

00:48:43.060 --> 00:48:44.060
your home.

00:48:44.060 --> 00:48:47.900
If you're a lady here this morning, Holly is here with a Bible and she'd take a Bible

00:48:47.900 --> 00:48:51.500
and show you how you too could know for sure that heaven is your home.

00:48:51.500 --> 00:48:57.620
We never want to embarrass anyone, but we want you to go to heaven when you die.

00:48:57.620 --> 00:49:01.780
Those that are saved, would you rejoice in what Christ has done for you?

00:49:01.780 --> 00:49:03.700
As Kimberly plays, the altar is open.

